|  |  | Nombre de GE-Frottis Realises |

|  |  | Nombre de GE-Frottis Positifs |
| PRES | Cas présumés de paludisme | Nombre total de cas de paludisme Presume |
| MALTREAT | Cas de paludisme traités | Nombre de cas de paludisme traités aux ACT |
| MALSIMP | Cas de paludisme simples | Nombre total de cas de paludisme Simple confirme |
| MALSEV | Cas de paludisme graves | Nombre de cas de paludisme grave confirme |
| MALDTH | Deces dus au paludisme | Nombre de décès dus au paludisme grave |
|  |  | Nombre de deces dus au paludisme grave |

| ALLOUT | Consultations ambulatoires toutes causes | Total Consultants |

7. ## **POPULATION DATA** {#population-data}

### **7.1 General introduction and scope** {#7.1-general-introduction-and-scope}

### **7.2 Investigate national population data from HMIS / NMDR** {#7.2-investigate-national-population-data-from-hmis-/-nmdr}

### **7.3 Investigate WORLDPOP population raster data** {#7.3-investigate-worldpop-population-raster-data}

#### \[Worldpop API Extract\] {#[worldpop-api-extract]-1}

Status: available  
Goal: quick download of available population data  
Description: Extracts worldpop raster data automatically through an API call and aggregates population data using country shapes file. Note that only 2020 raster data are available through the API call.

#### \[Worldpop Manual Extract\] {#[worldpop-manual-extract]}

Status: to be build  
Goal: obtain worldpop data from a year of choice  
Description: Extracts worldpop raster data from a manually downloaded raster file, and aggregates population data using country shapes file. User downloads manually worldpop raster data from a year of choice and pipeline allows to aggregate this population data to country shapes file.

### **7.4 Scale population sizes and estimate vulnerable population sizes** {#7.4-scale-population-sizes-and-estimate-vulnerable-population-sizes}

#### \[HMIS Population Transformation\] {#[hmis-population-transformation]}

Status: available  
Goal: population disaggregation for incidence and budget calculations  
Description: Using national population data, user can opt to scale these estimates using a manually provided total (e.g. UN total population size) and estimate as many levels of disaggregations as needed (e.g. U5, 1-2Y, 0-1Y etc.).
